  "text": "Study Populations: We primarily used data from 3 populations, YRI (Yoruba in Ibadan), CEU (Utah residents with Northern and Western European ancestry), and CHB (Han Chinese in Beijing) available from the 1000 Genome Project (1000 Genomes Project Consortium et al. 2012; [CITATION_1] . For the phylogenetic analysis, we also analyzed haplotypes of the chimpanzee reference genome (The Chimpanzee Sequencing Consortium 2005), the Neanderthal genome [CITATION_2] and Denisovan genome .",
